      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "In my case, I started out as a Java Developer about two decades ago. These days, I still keep in touch with coding - mostly for structuring data, pulling data from APIs for analysis, small automations, or integrations.\n\nWith the rise of AI, I find it amazing that I can now write programs in different languages with much more ease, and even understand or adapt scripts quickly.\n\nI’m curious - what about you?\n\nDo you still code in your TPM role?\n\nIf yes, in what context (automation, data analysis, side projects)?\n\nOr do you prefer to focus purely on leadership and program execution?\n\nWould love to hear your experiences!",
      "author": {
        "id": "1409829277557461043",
        "name": "rrvaluecreator",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "RR",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
